.TH RUN_SERVER "1" "December 2025" "202602020740-git" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
run_server \- Start an HTTP server from a directory
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B run_server
[\fI\,OPTIONS\/\fR] [\fI\,DIRECTORY\/\fR] [\fI\,PORT\/\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B run_server
is a script for quickly starting an HTTP server to serve files from a directory. It automatically detects available server tools and starts serving the specified directory.
.PP
The script is useful for quick file sharing, testing web pages, or serving static content.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-term
Open in a terminal window
.TP
.BR \-\-help
Display help message with usage information and available options
.TP
.BR \-\-config
Generate or regenerate user configuration file with default settings
.TP
.BR \-\-version
Show script version information and exit
.TP
.BR \-\-options
Display all available command-line options
.TP
.BR \-\-debug
Enable debug mode with verbose output and command tracing (set -x)
.TP
.BR \-\-raw
Disable colorized output for plain text display
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B run_server
Serve current directory on default port
.TP
.B run_server /var/www 8080
Serve /var/www on port 8080
.TP
.B run_server . 3000
Serve current directory on port 3000
.SH FILES
.TP
.B ~/.config/myscripts/run_server/settings.conf
User configuration file for run_server preferences
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success
.TP
.B 1
General error
.TP
.B 3
No server tool available
.SH NOTES
.IP \(bu 2
Detects python, php, ruby, or node servers
.IP \(bu 2
Default port is usually 8000 or 8080
.IP \(bu 2
Serves directory over HTTP
.SH DEPENDENCIES
.TP
.B Required (one of):
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
python3 - Python's http.server module
.IP \(bu 2
php - PHP's built-in server
.IP \(bu 2
ruby - Ruby's WEBrick
.IP \(bu 2
node - Node.js http-server
.RE
